The buffet evening meal was absolutely brilliant, best meal we've ever at as Disney Paris good choice of salad, starters and desserts too.  The breakfast was very average although waffles were nice, no full english, more continental but with boiled eggs and some bacon on offer.  There is a startbucks on site but not open til later on.  The resturant got really busy at breakfast and there was a long line by 7:15 so get there early if you want to use the extra magic hour.  When you get off the bus at the park you are opposite the train station, there is a starbucks and another cafe open very early where you can easily get breakfast to stay or coffee to take to the turnstyles so I wouldn't bother with hotel breakfast again.
